t out of favour."]},{"name":"Vivian","meanings":["Originally a boy's name, from an Old French form of the Latin name <i>Vivianus</i> (probably a derivative of <i>vivus</i> ‘alive’), but now more frequent as a girl's name. The name was borne by a 5th-century bishop of Saintes in western France, remembered for protecting his people during the invasion of the Visigoths."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1354684,"age":97,"year":"1200","julianDay":2159351,"description":"The Christian territory controlled the Kingdoms of Aragon, Navarre, and Castile.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"When Zerachya II Ha-Levi de Girona was born in 1103, in Spain, her father, Shesheht Beneviste Perfet Nasi, was 4 and her mother, Reina Bat bat Barzilai bat Mar Shealtiel, was 23. She had at least 3 sons with Rabeinu Zerachye or Zarhiya II HaRaza Halevi de su lista de precios."},"et":{"1103–":"1103–Surnud","1095–Female":"1095–Surnud","1103–Female":"1103–Surnud","1110–1226":"1110–1226","1115–1185":"1115–1185","1140–1205":"1140–1205","1147–Male":"1147–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1100–1209":"1100–1209","1080–Female":"1080–Surnud","1080":"1080","1110":"1110","1185":"1185","1140":"1140","1095":"1095","about 1140 or 1150":"umbes 1140","1205":"1205","1226":"1226","1115":"1115","1103":"1103","1147":"1147","1200":"1200","1100":"1100","1209":"1209","Catalonia, Spain":"Catalunya, Hispaania","Provence, France":"Provence, Prantsusmaa","Spain":"Hispaania"},"fi":{"1103–":"1103–Kuollut","1095–Female":"1095–Kuollut","1103–Female":"1103–Kuollut","1110–1226":"1110–1226","1115–1185":"1115–1185","1140–1205":"1140–1205","1147–Male":"1147–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1100–1209":"1100–1209","1080–Female":"1080–Kuollut","1080":"1080","1110":"1110","1185":"1185","1140":"1140","1095":"1095","about 1140 or 1150":"noin 1140","1205":"1205","1226":"1226","1115":"1115","1103":"1103","1147":"1147","1200":"1200","1100":"1100","1209":"1209","Catalonia, Spain":"Catalunya, Espanja","Provence, France":"Provence, Ranska","Spain":"Es